I don't agree with war... I don't agree with millions of innocent people dying, so that a whole country can be &quot;taught a lesson&quot;. I don't agree with terrorist bastards coming here and blowing up our buildings and killing our own, either... but they did it.<br>
<br>
If someone wants to be racist, or was raised to be racist, or isnt really racist but chooses to post comments about being racist, then that is thier opinion. They have that right, under the law. If it does not go against the &quot;freedom of speech&quot; clause, then those of us who disagree have a choice... we can argue the point, exercising our own freedom of speech, or we can ignore him/her, and hope they go away...<br>
<br>
Nobody is ever going to see completely eye to eye... it is human nature, and the way we were brought up and raised to think for ourselves, and form our own ideas and opinions on ANY subject out there.... doesn't mean we are wrong or right, it means we are human, and for the majority (I believe) it means we are American.<br>
<br>
For us to sit here and debate this issue, is fun, and interesting to read so many other views, both that I agree with and disagree with.. but it isn't going to change anything.... those who feel one way, are going to continue to feel that way long after this thread is dead... and those who disagree, are still going to disagree. That doesn't make them right, or wrong... it makes them human.<br>
<br>
As far as burning the CD's. after the &quot;comment&quot; made by the Dixie Chicks... I do believe, if I heard the story correctly, they did not &quot;flame&quot; the president in such a manner that it was illegal. From the quotes I heard, what she said was she was &quot;ashamed to come from the same STATE&quot;... not that she was ashamed to be an American... or anything else about the country in general...<br>
<br>
I don't agree with the statement, considering what our country was going through at the time, with the war in Iraq and people dying over there (both ours and thiers), but I wouldn't rush out and burn my copies of thier disc's either. I feel no differently about them now, as I did before. They felt thier opinion needed to be said, and they said it (or she did, I guess only one actually MADE the comment). I honestly believe the comment was only made to put themselves in the spotlight for those few moments, hours, days, or week.<br>
<br>
I guess what I'm tryin to say is, whether you agree with someone's opinion or not, it is thier opinion. You have the right to disagree, JUST AS MUCH as they have the right to that opinion to begin with.<br>
<br>
I am sorry if feelings were hurt, and feathers were rumpled by someone making racist statements... it seems to be general concenus that the statements were made for that reason alone... and getting upset and angry is only adding &quot;fuel to the fire&quot; and giving the person even more of a reason to post more such statements. If he/she posted for a reason, other than to get shit started... then maybe we should all step back, and give them the soap box for awhile... and let them get whatever views they feel need to be voiced, out, so we can all go on with our own ideas of how Freedom of Speech should be handled.<br>
<br>
