Aye, I agree.  My grandmother use to tell me that my right to the freedom to do what I wanted to do stopped where someone elses nose began.  (She's Greek...they are strange.)  But in an round about way that's my point.   Freedom's come with responsibilites.  But learning how to use those freedoms without ruining someone elses ability to enjoy THEIR freedoms is something no government can legislate.  That comes from your family, from your culture, from the people you listen to when you're sitting around the holiday table, or at a picnic with friends and those people who are important to you.  <br>
<br>
 I don't think it's a good idea to have a bunch of older mostly white, mostly rich men who were voted into power by 22% of the voting population trying to legislate morality between extramarital affairs to a country they are acutally a minority in.<br>
<br>
I just hate to see people so willing to give up what rights they have left because being responsible for those rights is too much work.  =/<br>
